                  <td width="420" valign="top"><div align="center"> 
                      <p><img src="images/featured%20presentation%20copy.jpg" width="475" height="320" border="0" usemap="#Map10"></p>
                      <p><font size="4" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>THE 
                        CLASSIC SCIENCE FICTION CHANNEL </strong></font></p>
                      <p align="left"><strong><font size="4" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Ooodles 
                        and ooodles of links to completely legal viewable and 
                        (sometimes) downloadable science fiction goodness. Everything 
                        I can find on the web, from full length feature films 
                        to old time radio shows, that has even a hint of science 
                        fiction in it has been gathered here. I don't host these 
                        materials, you can easily find them for yourself with 
                        just a little googling, but I thought it would be nice 
                        for everyone to have a single resource site. This section 
                        is also my answer to the so-called Sci Fi Channel that 
                        broadcasts everything but science fiction.</font></strong></p>
                      <p align="left"><strong><font size="4" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Enjoy!</font></strong></p>
                    </div>
                    <p align="left">&nbsp;</p></td>
                </tr>
                <tr> 
                  <td height="350" colspan="2" valign="top"><p align="justify"><font size="3" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><font size="2">This 
                      section started as a rant against 'skiffytube', otherwise 
                      known as the SciFi Channel. The rant was sufficient to get 
                      this page featured on BoinBoing.</font></strong></font></p>
                    <p align="justify"><font size="2"><strong><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">You 
                      can read all about it, as well as the companion The Day 
                      The Earth Stood Still To Watch The Original Movie Day over 
                      on the page about the corruption of SF classics.</font></strong></font></p>
                    <p align="justify"><font size="2"><strong><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Sources 
                      for this section are numerous and growing every day, but 
                      if you'd like to hunt these things out for yourself - check 
                      these out:</font></strong></font></p>
                    <p align="justify"><font size="2"><strong><font color="#333399" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://www.hulu.com" target="_blank">www.Hulu.com</a></font></strong></font></p>
                    <p align="justify"><font size="2"><strong><font color="#333399" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
                      <a href="http://www.internetarchive.com" target="_blank">www.InternetArchive.org</a></font></strong></font></p>
